projects.description: Codeup Capstone Team Project utilizing Natural Language Processing (NLP) to predict Michelin star ratings of Michelin awardee restaurants using Michelin Guide review text. Michelin Guide review text was obtained utilizing BeautifulSoup, and our best model was run with TF-IDF/Logistic Regression.
projects.title: Predicting Michelin Star Ratings utilizing Michelin Guide text and NLP techniques

projects.description: This project was created to examine crime data from the City of Boston. Specifically, this project focuses on examining crime data collected by the City of Boston and examining trends in fraud crime occurrences at several periods. The onset of the COVID pandemic and it's impact is seen through the visualization of this data, which leads to further questions about crime data forecasting before and after the pandemic, both within Fraud crimes and crime rates in general
projects.title: Boston Crime: Utilizing data for a time-series analysis of Fraud Crimes from 2015-Present

projects.description: K-Means Clustering: Examining Zillow 'Zestimate' Log Error using clustering techniques. This project utilized clustering techniques to explore data and identify significant clusters to use in modeling.
projects.title: Unsupervised Machine Learning: Zillow "Zestimate" Clustering Project

projects.description: This project created several supervised machine learning models to predict single-family home value from a Zillow dataset. In this project, I obtained and cleaned Zillow data before exploring the data and constructing visualizations of features that can predict a property's home price. After exploration, I utilized scaling to model several regression algorithms and evaluate their performance on training data. Finally, I selected my best model and evaluated its performance on testing data. Included in this project are several python files (Wrangle, Explore Model) which contain functions used to complete the project.
projects.title: Supervised Machine Learning: Utilizing Zillow Data and Regression Modeling to predict Single-Family Home Prices

projects.description: In this project, I utilized data from a telecommunications company to develop a supervised machine-learning model to predict customer "churn." Predicting Churn, when a customer leaves a company, is an important part of business data analytics. This project involved wrangling the data, preparing for exploration and modeling (including constructing visualizations), and developing several algorithms to predict customer churn. The best model was selected and run on test data--it's performance on that data is reflected in a predicts .CSV file within this repository.
projects.title: Supervised Machine Learning- Utilizing Classification to Predict Customer Churn from a Telecommunications Company
